### [Proverbs Chapter 28](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 28:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">pro 28:2</span></span>

But - By a wise and good prince.

[Proverbs 28:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">pro 28:3</span></span>

It like - Is like a violent rain or flood, which washes away the very
seeds in the earth. He is the worst of all oppressors.

[Proverbs 28:4](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">pro 28:4</span></span>

Contend - Are so far from praising them, that they severely reprove
them.

[Proverbs 28:5](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">pro 28:5</span></span>

Judgment - What is just and right. All things - Which are necessary to
be known by them.

[Proverbs 28:6](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">pro 28:6</span></span>

Better - In a much happier condition.

[Proverbs 28:10](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">pro 28:10</span></span>

Causeth - That by evil counsel, or example, or artifice, draws them into
evil.

[Proverbs 28:12](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#012.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_012">pro 28:12</span></span>

Rejoice - Are promoted. Glory - In that common - wealth. Rise - Are
advanced to authority. Hidden - Wise and good men, who only are worthy
of the name of men, withdraw themselves into obscure places.

[Proverbs 28:14](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">pro 28:14</span></span>

Alway - In all times, companies, and conditions.

[Proverbs 28:16](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">pro 28:16</span></span>

Oppressor - The tyranny of a prince, is a manifest sign of folly.
Prolong - By God's favour, the peace and satisfaction of his own mind,
and the hearty love of his people.

[Proverbs 28:17](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">pro 28:17</span></span>

Violence - That sheddeth any man's blood. Shall flee - Shall speedily be
destroyed. Shall slay - None should desire or endeavour to save him from
his deserved punishment.

[Proverbs 28:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">pro 28:18</span></span>

At once - Once for all; so he shall never rise more.

[Proverbs 28:20](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#020.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_020">pro 28:20</span></span>

Faithful - Who deals truly and justly in all his transactions.

[Proverbs 28:21](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">pro 28:21</span></span>

For - When a man hath once accustomed himself to take bribes, a very
small advantage will make him sell justice.

[Proverbs 28:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">pro 28:22</span></span>

Evil eye - Is uncharitable to persons in want, and envious to those who
get any thing besides him. Poverty - And consequently that he shall need
the pity and help of others.

[Proverbs 28:24](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#024.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_024">pro 28:24</span></span>

The same - Is a thief and robber.

[Proverbs 28:25](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#025.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_025">pro 28:25</span></span>

Fat - Shall live happily and comfortably.

[Proverbs 28:26](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">pro 28:26</span></span>

Wisely - Distrusting his own judgment, and seeking the advice of others,
and especially of God.

[Proverbs 28:28](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#028.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_028">pro 28:28</span></span>

Men - Righteous men are afraid to appear publickly.

